McDonald’s Europe President Resigns to Lead PizzaExpress

-- B y   L e s l i e   P a t t o n
-- 
2011-08-16T20:08:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/mcdonald-s-europe-president-resigns-to-lead-pizzaexpress-chain.html
McDonald’s Corp. (MCD)  said that Steve Easterbrook, president of the restaurant chain’s  Europe 
business, will resign to join closely held Gondola Group.  Douglas Goare, 59, executive vice president of McDonald’s
global supply chain and real estate development will take over
for Easterbrook effective Oct. 1, the  Oak Brook , Illinois-based
company said in a statement today. Easterbrook, 44, will become
the chief executive officer of London-based Gondola’s
PizzaExpress chain.  As president of McDonald’s Europe, Goare will oversee about
7,000 restaurants in 40 countries. Sales at European stores open
at least 13 months rose 5.3 percent in July. Analysts had
predicted a gain of 6.1 percent, the average of five estimates
compiled by Bloomberg News.  The company fell 15 cents to $86.67 at 4 p.m. in New York
Stock Exchange composite trading. The shares have gained 13
percent this year.  McDonald’s, led by Chief Executive James Skinner, has more
than 33,000 stores worldwide.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leslie Patton in Chicago at 
